    <div class="breadcrumbs">
        <a href="/l1/springfield/">Home</a> &gt; 
        <a href="/l1/springfield/guides">Guides</a> &gt; 
        Fence Permit
    </div>
    
    <main>
        <article>
            <h1>Fence Permit Requirements</h1>
            
            <div class="alert-warning">
                <strong>Permit Temporarily Suspended</strong><br>
                Due to a high volume of applications and staffing limitations, new fence permit applications are currently suspended. We anticipate reopening the application process by Q3 2024. For questions, please contact the Building Department at (555) 123-4567.
            </div>
            
            <p>This guide provides information about obtaining a permit for fence installation or replacement in the City of Springfield.</p>
            
            <h2>When is a Permit Required?</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Any fence over 6 feet in height</li>
                <li>Fences in front yards (regardless of height)</li>
                <li>Pool fences (must meet specific safety requirements)</li>
                <li>Commercial property fences</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h2>Permit Fees</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Standard fence permit: $75</li>
                <li>Pool fence permit: $50</li>
                <li>Expedited review: Additional $35</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h2>Height Restrictions</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Front yard: Maximum 4 feet</li>
                <li>Side yard: Maximum 6 feet</li>
                <li>Rear yard: Maximum 6 feet</li>
                <li>Corner lots have additional visibility requirements</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h2>Required Documents</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Property survey showing fence location</li>
                <li>Site plan with dimensions</li>
                <li>Fence specification sheet (materials, height)</li>
                <li>Neighbor notification (for shared property lines)</li>
            </ul>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>Note:</strong> While the permit application is suspended, you may still submit a fence repair application for existing fences that do not meet the above criteria.
            </div>
            
            <h2>Apply for a Fence Repair Permit</h2>
            <p>If your project involves repairing an existing fence (not installation or replacement), you may still apply:</p>
            <p><a href="/l1/springfield/apply/fence-repair">Fence Repair Application</a></p>
        </article>
    </main>
    
